cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "BitWise-LLM-Forge: First-Principles Implementations of Modern LLM Architectures"
message: "If you use this repository, please cite it as below."
authors:
  - family-names: "Kılıç"
    given-names: "Haydar"
repository-code: "https://github.com/HAYDARKILIC/bitwise-llm-forge"
url: "https://github.com/HAYDARKILIC/bitwise-llm-forge"
abstract: >
  A graduate-level, six-week curriculum portfolio implementing modern
  large-language-model optimization techniques from first principles in pure
  PyTorch — BitNet b1.58 ternary weights, Test-Time Training layers,
  differentiable logic networks, FlashAttention-style tiling, Rotary
  Position Embedding with YaRN context extension, and an end-to-end
  hardware-friendly miniature LLM. Produced for the course "Advanced LLM
  Architectures & Optimization".
keywords:
  - "large language models"
  - "quantization"
  - "BitNet"
  - "flash attention"
  - "RoPE"
  - "test-time training"
  - "differentiable logic"
  - "from-scratch implementation"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: 2025-01-01
